node.text: Liliana Vazquez, '20, became the first person in her family to graduate from college when she earned her bachelor's degree in education sciences and psychology & social behavior from UCI this spring. In this video, she reads a letter to her mother, thanking her for the unconditional love, support and motivation she has provided throughout her educational journey. Let's hear it for the family, friends and mentors who provide such valuable support to our first-gen students! 🎉 🎓

node.text:
The UCI Rowing team practices balance and flexibility with a yoga session in Aldrich Park. 🚣🏽‍♂️🧘🏽‍♀️💙💛

For this #WellnessWednesday, @ucirvinerowing shares how they incorporate yoga in their training regimen: 

"Rowing is a dynamic sport that’s uses 85 percent of the muscles in the body. Here at UCI we believe in balance. While we mostly train on the water in Newport Beach out of the UCI Boathouse we like to take a break and visit campus in the early morning to enjoy the peacefulness of nature that Aldrich Park provides. In our yoga practice we focus on breathing methodology, mobility, and injury prevention." 

Photo and caption: @ucirvinerowing

Anteaters, how do you maintain balance in your mind and body?
